        "p",
        {},
        "In Greek, almost every noun is preceded by an",
        " ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "article"
        ],
        ". The article tells us the gender, number, and case of the noun.\n            There are two types:",
        " ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "Definite"
        ],
        " ",
        "(\"the\") and",
        " ",
        [
          "strong",
          {},
          "Indefinite"
        ],
        " ",
        "(\"a/an\")."
      ],
      [
        "h2",
        {},
        "1. The Definite Article (Το Οριστικό Άρθρο)"
      ],
      [
        "p",
        {},
        "This is used when referring to a specific item. In English, we only\n            have \"the\", but in Greek, it changes based on gender."
